As of the [[1367 DR|Year of the Shield, 1367 DR]], there was a little-known village of [[gnomes]] and [[dwarves]] among the ruins at the intersection of Skuldask Road and Thundar's Ride called [[Tempus's Tears]]. Travel along the road was relatively safe because patrols of [[Hellriders]] from Elturel traveled this road every four hours or so, even at night. South of Elturel, the patrols ended at [[Windstream Lodge]] (one of their outposts).

As of the [[1372 DR|Year of Wild Magic, 1372 DR]], the "leaf farm" owned by [[Tatha Beruel]], called [[Aloum Lyndren]], was located just north of Skuldask Road a few miles west of Elturel.{{Cite dragon/301/Elminster's Guide to the Realms: Tatha's Broomworks|74}}
